'''[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]'''已经影响了全世界对'''[[社会化媒体|社交媒体]]'''的使用。[[社交網路服務|社交网络服务]]被用来传播信息，人们通过[[網路迷因|互联网迷因]]，从大流行中寻找幽默，以此转移对疫情过于担心的注意力。<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=Facebook struggles with high traffic as the world sits at home and takes to social media because of Covid-19|trans-title=由于Covid-19，Facebook面临着高流量的困扰，因为全世界都坐在家里使用社交媒体|url=https://www.msn.com/en-in/news/other/facebook-struggles-with-high-traffic-as-world-sits-at-home-and-takes-to-social-media-because-of-covid-19/ar-BB11Gra4|accessdate=2020-03-26|author=|date=|format=|work=www.msn.com|publisher=|language=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326001022/https://www.msn.com/en-in/news/other/facebook-struggles-with-high-traffic-as-world-sits-at-home-and-takes-to-social-media-because-of-covid-19/ar-BB11Gra4|archivedate=2020-03-26|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|script-title="We Need the Joy to Survive": Naomi Shimada on How to Mindfully Use Social Media in the Age of Social Distancing|trans-title=“我们需要生存的喜悦”：岛田直美（Naomi Shimada）谈在社交化时代如何精打细算地使用社交媒体|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/naomi-shimada-mixed-feelings-social-media-interview|accessdate=2020-03-26|author=Okwodu|date=|first=Janelle|format=|work=Vogue|publisher=|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326001022/https://www.vogue.com/article/naomi-shimada-mixed-feelings-social-media-interview|archivedate=2020-03-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>

疫情期间，社交媒体的使用量急剧增加，这在很大程度上是因为许多政府鼓励采取了[[保持人身距離|保持人身距離]]措施。很多人被要求待在家里，所以他们只能转向社交媒体来维持他们的[[人際關係|人際關係]]并获得娱乐来打发时间。 此外，隔离迫使许多人改变了生活方式，这也许会给他们的[[心理健康|心理健康]]带来负面的影响。<ref name=":02">{{Cite web|script-title=COVID-19: Social media use goes up as the country stays indoors|trans-title=COVID-19：随着国家/地区在室内，社交媒体的使用率将上升|url=https://www.vicnews.com/news/covid-19-social-media-use-goes-up-as-country-stays-indoors/|accessdate=2020-04-15|author=|date=2020-03-31|format=|work=Victoria News|publisher=|language=en-US|dead-url=no|archive-date=2020-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404010731/https://www.vicnews.com/news/covid-19-social-media-use-goes-up-as-country-stays-indoors/}}</ref>因此，许多使用社交媒体的在线咨询服务浮出了水面，并且开始流行起来，将精神卫生工作者与需要他们的人联系起来。<ref>{{cite web|script-title=WES for Youth Online sees surge in counseling service use|trans-title=WES for Youth Online咨询服务的使用量出现激增|url=https://www.owensoundsuntimes.com/news/local-news/wes-for-youth-online-sees-surge-in-counselling-service-use|accessdate=|author=|date=2020-04-09|last=Gowan|first=Rob|format=|publisher=|language=en-US|dead-url=no|website=Owen Sound Sun Times|access-date=2020-04-15|archive-date=2020-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412190926/https://www.owensoundsuntimes.com/news/local-news/wes-for-youth-online-sees-surge-in-counselling-service-use}}</ref>

== 使用量增加 ==
=== 短信和视频通话服务 ===
多家社交媒体网站表示，居家隔离政策实施后，社交媒体的使用量骤增。因为大家暂时无法跟朋友和家人面对面的联系，社交媒体暂时成为了维系宝贵联系的主要沟通方式。比如，[[Facebook|Facebook]]的分析部门报告称，在2020年3月的最后一个月里，整体消息传递的增长超过了50%。WhatsApp的使用率也增长了40%。<ref name=":02" />2020年3月，TikTok（[[抖音|抖音]]国际版）的全球下载量比2月增长了5%。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/coronavirus-quarantine-appears-to-be-driving-a-global-tiktok-download-boom/|script-title=Coronavirus quarantine appears to be driving a global TikTok download boom|trans-title=冠状病毒隔离似乎正在推动全球TikTok下载热潮|last=Stassen|first=Murray|date=2020-03-24|work=Music Business Worldwide|accessdate=2020-09-25|archive-date=2020-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200824015906/https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/coronavirus-quarantine-appears-to-be-driving-a-global-tiktok-download-boom/|dead-url=no|author=|publisher=|language=|format=}}</ref>一项名为QuarantineChat的新服务在2020年3月1日推出，之后，随机报告显示加入此服务的用户在一个月内超过了1.5万名。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lockwood|first=Devi|date=2020-05-27|script-title=QuarantineChat Brings Back Spontaneity (and Distraction)|trans-title=QuarantineChat使自发性（和注意力分散）|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/27/arts/quarantinechat-virus.html|access-date=2020-07-08|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200703212052/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/27/arts/quarantinechat-virus.html|dead-url=no|author=|publisher=|accessdate=|format=}}</ref>

Facebook、Twitter和YouTube都增加了对[[垃圾邮件|垃圾邮件]]过滤器的依赖，因为负责处理内容的工作人员无法出门工作。<ref>{{Cite journal|script-title=Coronavirus Disrupts Social Media's First Line of Defense|trans-title=冠状病毒破坏了社交媒体的第一道防线|author=Louise Matsakis, Paris Martineau|url=https://www.wired.com/story/coronavirus-social-media-automated-content-moderation/|journal=Wired|accessdate=2020-03-25|issue=|doi=|others=|year=|volume=|page=|pmid=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322000250/https://www.wired.com/story/coronavirus-social-media-automated-content-moderation/|archivedate=2020-03-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 在线咨询服务 ===
特别是在病毒感染最严重的国家，比如说中国，在线[[心理健康|心理健康]]咨询服务的需求激增。 由于2019COVID-19大流行给大家带来了很多不可抵抗的困难和计划外的改变，生活方式的忽然改变使大家感到害怕和不安。在中国，心理医生利用微信、微博和[[抖音|抖音]]等社交媒体[[App|App]]推出了在线心理健康教育项目。<ref>{{Cite journal|script-title=Online mental health services in China during the COVID-19 outbreak |trans-title=COVID-19爆发期间中国的在线心理健康服务|url=|first1=Shuai|last2=Yang|first2=Lulu|date=April 2020|journal=The Lancet Psychiatry|issue=4|doi=10.1016/S2215-0366(20)30077-8|others=|year=|volume=7|page=|pages=e17–e18|language=en|pmc=7129099|pmid=32085841|last3=Zhang|first3=Chenxi|last4=Xiang|first4=Yu-Tao|last5=Liu|first5=Zhongchun|last6=Hu|first6=Shaohua|last7=Zhang|first7=Bin|last1=Liu}}</ref>在[[加拿大|加拿大]]，[[艾伯塔省|阿尔伯塔省]]政府启动了一项5300万加元的2019COVID-19精神健康应对计划，其中包括增加现有热线电话的利用率。<ref>{{cite web|script-title=Alberta launches $53M COVID-19 mental health response plan|trans-title=艾伯塔省启动5300万加元的COVID-19精神健康应对计划|url=https://chatnewstoday.ca/2020/04/15/alberta-launches-53m-covid-19-mental-health-response-plan/|accessdate=|author=|date=|last=Brown|first=Chris|format=|publisher=|language=en|website=CHAT News Today|access-date=2020-04-16|archive-date=2022-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220421055114/https://chatnewstoday.ca/2020/04/15/alberta-launches-53m-covid-19-mental-health-response-plan/}}</ref>在[[安大略省|安大略省]]，政府提供了高达1200万美元的紧急资金，用于扩大在线和虚拟精神健康支持。<ref>{{cite web|script-title=Ontario Increasing Mental Health Support During|trans-title=COVID-19安大略省在COVID-19期间增加精神卫生支持|url=https://news.ontario.ca/opo/en/2020/04/ontario-increasing-mental-health-support-during-covid-19.html|accessdate=|author=|date=|format=|publisher=|language=en|dead-url=no|website=news.ontario.ca|access-date=2020-04-16|archive-date=2020-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200421012252/https://news.ontario.ca/opo/en/2020/04/ontario-increasing-mental-health-support-during-covid-19.html}}</ref>

==== 对心理健康的影响 ====
大量的[[心理学|心理学]]研究证明，与外界的联系可以增强归属感和心理社会幸福感，从而增强心理健康，减少[[焦虑症|焦虑]]和[[重性抑鬱疾患|重度抑郁]]的风险。<ref>{{Cite journal|script-title=Social Media Use and Social Connectedness in Adolescents: The Positives and the Potential Pitfalls |trans-title=青少年的社交媒体使用和社交联系：积极因素和潜在的陷阱|author=|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/product/identifier/S0816512214000029/type/journal_article|last=Allen|first=Kelly A.|last2=Ryan|first2=Tracii|date=July 2014|journal=The Australian Educational and Developmental Psychologist|issue=1|doi=10.1017/edp.2014.2|others=|year=|volume=31|page=|pages=18–31|language=en|issn=0816-5122|pmid=|last3=Gray|first3=DeLeon L.|last4=McInerney|first4=Dennis M.|last5=Waters|first5=Lea}}</ref>

信息过载和不断使用社交媒体已被证明与抑郁和焦虑的增加呈正相关。<ref>{{Cite journal|script-title=Mental health problems and social media exposure during COVID-19 outbreak |trans-title=COVID-19爆发期间的心理健康问题和社交媒体曝光|author=|url=|first1=Junling|last2=Zheng|first2=Pinpin|date=2020-04-16|journal=PLOS ONE|issue=4|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0231924|others=|year=|volume=15|page=|pages=e0231924|language=en|bibcode=2020PLoSO..1531924G|issn=1932-6203|pmc=7162477|pmid=32298385|last3=Jia|first3=Yingnan|last4=Chen|first4=Hao|last5=Mao|first5=Yimeng|last6=Chen|first6=Suhong|last7=Wang|first7=Yi|last8=Fu|first8=Hua|last9=Dai|first9=Junming|last1=Gao}}</ref>

==== 对在线业务的影响 ====
冠状病毒大流行迅速蔓延，许多企业关闭，许多工人失业或在家工作。 为了防止COVID-19扩散，每个家庭都需要自行隔离，而这使当今的在线业务处于相当有利的地位。许多企业主抱怨没有客户，失去了销售额，而网站设计良好的企业为客户提供的服务比以往都要多。

==== 对视觉艺术的影响 ====
