在土耳其，有400多人因在社交媒体上发布有关大流行的“挑衅性”信息而被捕。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-turkey-idUSKBN21C1SG|script-title=Turkey rounds up hundreds for social media posts about coronavirus|trans-title=土耳其在社交媒体上发布了数百篇有关冠状病毒的文章|newspaper=Reuters|date=2020-03-25|via=www.reuters.com|access-date=2020-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325150956/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-turkey-idUSKBN21C1SG|archive-date=2020-03-25|dead-url=no|author=|work=|publisher=|accessdate=|language=|format=}}</ref> 据报道，自2019年12月31日以来，中国社交媒体网络（如[[微信|微信]]）审查了与大流行有关的任何术语，尤其值得一提的是，[[李文亮|李文亮]]医生因在聊天软件中发布有关疫情的消息而受到[[武汉市|武汉]]警方的警告。<ref name=":1">{{cite web|script-title=Internet Censorship During COVID-19 Is Threat To Cryptocurrencies And Liberty|trans-title=COVID-19期间的互联网审查对加密货币和自由构成威胁|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/rogerhuang/2020/03/29/internet-censorship-during-covid-19-is-threat-to-cryptocurrencies-and-liberty/|accessdate=|author=|date=|last=Huang|first=Roger|format=|publisher=|language=en|website=Forbes|access-date=2020-04-20|archive-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117113513/https://www.forbes.com/sites/rogerhuang/2020/03/29/internet-censorship-during-covid-19-is-threat-to-cryptocurrencies-and-liberty/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 地方政府告知中国医生，应在社交媒体上删除呼吁捐赠医疗用品的帖子。<ref>{{cite web|script-title=Chinese 'hero' doctor dies, unleashing public fury at Beijing|trans-title=中国“英雄”医生去世，在北京引发公众愤怒|url=https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Asia-Pacific/2020/0207/Chinese-hero-doctor-dies-unleashing-public-fury-at-Beijing|accessdate=|author=|date=2020-02-07|last=McDonald|first=Joe|format=|publisher=|language=|website=Christian Science Monitor|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117113516/https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Asia-Pacific/2020/0207/Chinese-hero-doctor-dies-unleashing-public-fury-at-Beijing|archive-date=2021-01-17|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>

